Bring a #medium pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are
pre-sliced!). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced thin),
separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1}.

Melt @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; cook, stirring, until golden and
toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Cook
until just fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn
off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all
over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan
used for panko over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn
off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high
heat. Stir in mushrooms and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium.

Once mushrooms are browned and tender, add @gnocchi{8.8%ounce} to #pot{} of
boiling water. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain.

Stir scallion whites, remaining garlic powder, and @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4
servings) into pan with mushrooms. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, half the
@Parmesan cheese{1/8%cup} (save the rest for serving), and @water{1/3%cup} (1/2
cup for 4). Cook, stirring, until combined and creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off
heat.

Stir in tomato, another @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4), and @truffle zest{2%g}
to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir drained gnocchi into pan with sauce until thoroughly coated, adding water a
splash at a time until sauce reaches a creamy consistency.

Divide between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan.

Sprinkle with as much garlicky panko as you like and serve.

> Serve chicken atop gnocchi.